Weather officials say while the rain has dwindled, motorists are urged to be careful on the roads. JOHANNESBURG - Heavy rains have been experienced across South Africa on Friday. It's led to the flooding of roads. READ: Heavy rains: 3 die in KZN, province on high alert In the south of Johannesburg, there have been severe thunderstorms and strong winds. A hospital in Alberton has been severely affected. READ: KZN disaster management on high alert for heavy rains To the east, roads in Benoni were also flooded due to the severe rain. People have been posting pictures of icy-looking hail on social media. Weather officials say while the rain has dwindled, motorists are urged to be careful on the roads.